 election]] and Members of the 5th National Assembly for Wales\n*[[List of Welsh Assembly by-elections]]\n*[[National Assembly for Wales constituencies and electoral regions]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{Welsh AMs 2016-2021|state=collapsed}}\n[[Category:Wales AMs 2016\u20132021|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of members of the National Assembly for Wales]]\n[[Category:National Assembly for Wales]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}\n\n{| id=toc style=\"float:right\"\n|[[Members of the 1st National Assembly for Wales|1st Assembly]]\n|([[1999 National Assembly for Wales election|1999]])\n|-\n|[[Members of the 2nd National Assembly for Wales|2nd Assembly]]\n|([[2003 National Assembly for Wales election|2003]])\n|-\n|[[Members of the 3rd National Assembly for Wales|3rd Assembly]]\n|([[2007 National Assembly for Wales election|2007]])\n|-\n|[[Members of the 4th National Assembly for Wales|4th Assembly]]\n|([[2011 National Assembly for Wales election|2011]])\n|-\n|'''5th Assembly'''\n|([[2016 National Assembly for Wales election|2016]])\n|-\n|[[Members of the 6th Welsh Parliament|''6th Parliament'']]\n|''([[2021 Welsh Parliament election|2021]])''\n|}\n\nThis is a list of '''[[Member of the National Assembly for Wales|Assembly Members]]''' (AMs) or, in [[Welsh language|Welsh]], '''''Aelodau'r Cynulliad (ACau)''''' elected to the fifth [[National Assembly for Wales]] at the [[2016 National Assembly for Wales election|2016 election]]. Of the 60 members 40 were elected from [[first past the post]] [[National Assembly for Wales constituencies and electoral regions|constituencies]] with a further 20 members being returned from five [[National Assembly for Wales constituencies and electoral regions|regions]], each electing four AMs through [[mixed member proportional representation]].\n\n== Composition of the Assembly ==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=